OL,4,Ccouncillors, despite calls to step down
OL,6,FBy-elections cost extra money for
OL,7,Falready cash-strapped councils and
OL,8,Falso mean voter turnout is likely to
OL,9,Fbe a lot lower. But some serve in
OL,10,Fwards where other local elections are
OL,11,Ftaking place in May - meaning the
OL,12,Fpotential extra cost would be lower.
OL,14,FWhile all of the nine Labour MPs also
OL,15,Fworking as councillors have given up
OL,16,Ftheir #12,000 a year councillor
OL,17,Fallowance, 14 of 26 MPs are still
OL,18,Freceiving some kind of payment on top
OL,19,Fof their #94,000 a year MP salary.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/19
